memory://ace_framework.summary: ACE (Agentic Context Engineering) is a framework that enhances LLM performance by managing and evolving adaptive contexts through modular generation, reflection, and curation, preventing context collapse and brevity bias while improving agent and domain-specific task outcomes with lower overhead.

memory://expert_dl_profile.summary: This memory profile outlines expert practices and standards for deep learning, LLM, and diffusion model development using PyTorch, Transformers, Diffusers, and Gradio.

memory://ace-framework-philosophy.summary: ACE Framework enables self-improving AI agents through a three-agent system (generator, reflector, curator) that dynamically updates a knowledge playbook to reduce errors and improve performance without manual fine-tuning.

memory://ace-implementation-principles.summary: This file outlines ACE implementation principles for Delia, focusing on atomic updates, feedback-driven learning, semantic deduplication, hybrid retrieval, and per-project isolation in LLM-powered workflows.

memory://anthropic-context-engineering.summary: The document outlines strategies for effective context engineering in AI agents by minimizing context size, using just-in-time retrieval, and structuring memory and tools to maximize performance while avoiding context overload.
exports: Long-horizon task techniques (compaction, structured note-taking, sub-agent architectures)

memory://ace-component-design.summary: This file outlines the design of missing ACE Framework components (Reflector, Curator, Semantic Deduplication, Hybrid Retrieval) for task analysis and bullet management using reflection, curation, and semantic techniques.
